1 target areas that actively contribute to the educational, civic, and social lives of the residents
2 of Louisiana; and
3 WHEREAS, the current international program, Soaring to Greater Heights of Service
4 and Sisterhood, has five initiatives: Empower Our Families; Build Our Economic Wealth;
5 Enhance Our Environment; Advocate for Social Justice; and Uplift Our Local Community;
6 and
7 WHEREAS, in addition, the sorority collaborates with Soles 4 Souls and Lions Club
8 International and continues to focus on breast cancer awareness and heart health; and
9 WHEREAS, the women of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority, Incorporated, are
10 committed to making a positive impact upon campuses, communities, our nation, and the
11 world in various ways by making and sending dresses and shirts to girls and boys in Haiti;
12 providing support to organizations that assist refugees and their families with integrating into
13 American life; saluting the Harlem Renaissance; providing guidance on care for the
14 caregivers, credit repair and monitoring, or entrepreneurship and the black dollar; assisting
15 high school students demystify the college admissions and enrollment process; and
16 developing emerging young leaders through mentoring programs throughout the nation; and
17 WHEREAS, AKA Day at the Louisiana State Capitol is a national program through
18 which Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority members throughout the nation meet with their
19 legislators to address issues that are pertinent to their communities; and
20 WHEREAS, it is appropriate to commend the members of Alpha Kappa Alpha
21 Sorority, Incorporated, for one hundred sixteen years of exemplary leadership and
22 outstanding community service, and to designate Tuesday, April 14, 2026, as AKA Day at
23 the Louisiana State Capitol.
24 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
25 does hereby designate Tuesday, April 14, 2026, as AKA Day at the Louisiana State Capitol
26 and does hereby commend and express enduring appreciation to the members of Alpha
27 Kappa Alpha Sorority, Incorporated, for their exemplary leadership and outstanding
28 community service and for the tremendous honor and pride these women bring to their
29 families, friends, communities, the state of Louisiana, and our nation and to communities
30 across the globe.
